## 8. Cross-family convergence threshold and minority preservation

Convergence threshold: for substantive moves (MAD v4 spec amendment; new normative clause; engine-v bump), 3-of-4 cross-family convergence suffices IF at least one non-Claude perspective (P3 or P4) is on the prevailing side. If both non-Claude perspectives dissent, the prevailing Claude-only position must be downgraded to non-substantive OR deferred to a future session.

